{
  "topicId": "m3-t2",
  "title": "Asking about Times and Appointments",
  "dialect": "levantine",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'What time is it?'"
        },
        "text": "The most common way to ask 'What time is it?' in Levantine Arabic is to use 'شو الساعة؟' or 'قديش الساعة؟'. Both are widely understood and used interchangeably.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شو الساعة؟",
            "english": "What time is it?",
            "transliteration": "Shu as-saa'a?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "قديش الساعة؟",
            "english": "What time is it? (literally: How much is the hour?)",
            "transliteration": "Qaddēsh as-saa'a?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Telling Basic Hours (1-12)"
        },
        "text": "To tell the time, you usually start with 'الساعة...' (as-saa'a...), meaning 'The time is...' or 'It is...', followed by the number of the hour. Note that 'واحد' (waḥad) changes to 'وحدة' (waḥdeh) when referring to 'one o'clock' in feminine form for 'الساعة'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة وحدة.",
            "english": "It is one o'clock.",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a waḥdeh."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة تْنَين.",
            "english": "It is two o'clock.",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a tnen."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة خَمسة.",
            "english": "It is five o'clock.",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a khamse."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "'O'clock' / Exactly on the Hour"
        },
        "text": "To specify that it's exactly on the hour, you can add 'بالزبط' (biz-zabt) or 'تماماً' (tamāman) after the hour. 'بالزبط' is more common in spoken Levantine.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة ستة بالزبط.",
            "english": "It is six o'clock sharp.",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a sitteh biz-zabt."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة تسعة تماماً.",
            "english": "It is nine o'clock exactly.",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a tis'a tamāman."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "شو الساعة بالزبط؟",
        "english": "What time is it exactly?",
        "transliteration": "Shu as-saa'a biz-zabt?"
      }
    },
    {
