    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Half Past (ونص)"
        },
        "text": "To express 'half past' the hour (e.g., 3:30), you say the hour followed by 'ونص' (w nuṣṣ), meaning 'and a half'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة وحدة ونص.",
            "english": "It is one thirty (half past one).",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a waḥdeh w nuṣṣ."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة سبعة ونص.",
            "english": "It is seven thirty (half past seven).",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a sab'a w nuṣṣ."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "A Quarter Past (وربع)"
        },
        "text": "To express 'a quarter past' the hour (e.g., 4:15), you say the hour followed by 'وربع' (w rubu'), meaning 'and a quarter'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة تلاتة وربع.",
            "english": "It is three fifteen (a quarter past three).",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a tlateh w rubu'."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة تمانة وربع.",
            "english": "It is eight fifteen (a quarter past eight).",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a tmāneh w rubu'."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "A Quarter To (إلا ربع)"
        },
        "text": "To express 'a quarter to' the hour (e.g., 5:45), you say the *next* hour followed by 'إلا ربع' (illa rubu'), meaning 'except a quarter'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة أربعة إلا ربع.",
            "english": "It is three forty-five (a quarter to four).",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a arba'a illa rubu'."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة عشرة إلا ربع.",
            "english": "It is nine forty-five (a quarter to ten).",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a 'ashra illa rubu'."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
