    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Adding Specific Minutes (1-29)"
        },
        "text": "For minutes from 1 to 29, you say the hour followed by 'و' (w, 'and') and the number of minutes (دقيقة - daqīqa for singular, دقايق - daqāyiq for plural).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة وحدة و خمس دقايق.",
            "english": "It is one five.",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a waḥdeh w khamas daqāyiq."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة تسعة و عشرين دقيقة.",
            "english": "It is nine twenty.",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a tis'a w 'ishrīn daqīqa."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Subtracting Specific Minutes (31-59)"
        },
        "text": "For minutes from 31 to 59, you say the *next* hour followed by 'إلا' (illa, 'except' or 'to') and the number of minutes remaining until the next hour.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة تلاتة إلا عشر دقايق.",
            "english": "It is two fifty (ten to three).",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a tlateh illa 'ashar daqāyiq."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة سبعة إلا خمس وعشرين دقيقة.",
            "english": "It is six thirty-five (twenty-five to seven).",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a sab'a illa khamas w 'ishrīn daqīqa."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Time of Day Markers"
        },
        "text": "To clarify AM/PM or general time of day, you can add words like 'صباحاً' (ṣabāḥan - in the morning), 'بعد الظهر' (ba'd iḍ-ḍuhur - afternoon), 'المسا' (il-masa - evening), or 'ليلاً' (laylan - at night).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة تسعة صباحاً.",
            "english": "It is nine AM (nine in the morning).",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a tis'a ṣabāḥan."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة أربعة المسا.",
            "english": "It is four PM (four in the evening).",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a arba'a il-masa."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة تْنَين بعد الظهر.",
            "english": "It is two PM (two in the afternoon).",
            "transliteration": "As-saa'a tnen ba'd iḍ-ḍuhur."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
