    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'When is the appointment?'"
        },
        "text": "To ask about the time of an appointment, you can use 'إيمتى الموعد؟' (ēmta l-maw'id?) or 'متى الموعد؟' (mata l-maw'id?). 'إيمتى' is more common in spoken Levantine.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "إيمتى الموعد؟",
            "english": "When is the appointment?",
            "transliteration": "Ēmta l-maw'id?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "متى الموعد تبعك؟",
            "english": "When is your appointment?",
            "transliteration": "Mata l-maw'id taba'ak?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Stating the Appointment Time"
        },
        "text": "To state the appointment time, you say 'الموعد الساعة...' (al-maw'id as-saa'a...), followed by the time, using the time-telling structures you've learned.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الموعد الساعة تسعة الصبح.",
            "english": "The appointment is at nine AM.",
            "transliteration": "Al-maw'id as-saa'a tis'a iṣ-ṣubḥ."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الموعد الساعة أربعة ونص بعد الظهر.",
            "english": "The appointment is at four thirty PM.",
            "transliteration": "Al-maw'id as-saa'a arba'a w nuṣṣ ba'd iḍ-ḍuhur."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
