          "english": "Asking 'Do you have an appointment?'"
        },
        "text": "To ask if someone has an appointment, you can say 'عندَك موعد؟' (indak maw'id?) for a male, or 'عندِك موعد؟' (indik maw'id?) for a female. The 'k' sound changes based on gender, indicated by diacritics.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "عندَك موعد؟ (to a male)",
            "english": "Do you have an appointment?",
            "transliteration": "Indak maw'id?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "عندِك موعد؟ (to a female)",
            "english": "Do you have an appointment?",
            "transliteration": "Indik maw'id?"
          }
        ]
      }
